♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.578 --> 01:43.712
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.842 --> 01:46.976
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:02.992 --> 02:07.997
-[CROWD CHATTERING]

02:20.662 --> 02:21.924
-I CAN'T BELIEVE
THEY'RE BUILDING

02:22.054 --> 02:23.621
AN OIL PLATFORM OFF ZUMA,

02:23.752 --> 02:25.406
EVEN IF IT IS UNDERWATER.

02:25.536 --> 02:27.799
IT'S NOT ABOUT THE VIEW,
IT'S ABOUT THE ENVIRONMENT.

02:28.974 --> 02:29.845
MATT?

02:30.889 --> 02:32.021
MATT, ARE YOU LISTENING TO ME?

02:32.152 --> 02:33.414
-MAN: THAT'S GOOD RIGHT THERE!

02:35.894 --> 02:37.026
-HUH?

02:37.722 --> 02:39.420
-IF YOU WANNA PLAY PRO
VOLLEYBALL SO BADLY,

02:39.550 --> 02:40.856
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
ENTER THE TOURNAMENT?

02:40.986 --> 02:42.292
-'CAUSE YOU JUST CAN'T ENTER.

02:42.423 --> 02:44.468
THIS IS ONE OF THE
STOPS FROM THE PRO TOUR.

02:44.599 --> 02:47.515
YOU HAVE TO RANKED OR WIN
A QUALIFYING TOURNAMENT.

02:48.037 --> 02:49.517
BESIDES, I DON'T HAVE PARTNER.

02:49.647 --> 02:51.258
-FINE.

02:51.388 --> 02:52.911
KEEP MAKING EXCUSES AND
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA FIND OUT

02:53.042 --> 02:53.956
IF YOU'RE GOOD
ENOUGH TO MAKE IT.

02:54.086 --> 02:55.740
-I'M NOT MAKING ANY EXCUSES.

02:55.871 --> 02:57.481
AND IF I DID MAKE
IT ON THE PRO TOUR,

02:57.612 --> 02:59.614
I'D HAVE TO QUIT
BEING A LIFEGUARD.

02:59.744 --> 03:01.355
-WELL THAT WON'T BE
A PROBLEM, WILL IT?

03:01.877 --> 03:03.270
'CAUSE YOU WON'T HAVE
TO MAKE THAT CHOICE.

03:08.318 --> 03:10.233
-SCAT HOVERCRAFT
IS THE VERY LATEST

03:10.364 --> 03:12.061
IN RESCUE VEHICLE TECHNOLOGY.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.368
IT'S BEEN USED EFFECTIVELY
IN SWIFT WATER,

03:14.498 --> 03:17.588
FLOODS, THIN ICE
RESCUES, RIVER RAPIDS.

03:18.763 --> 03:19.895
-BUT NOT OCEANS.

03:21.679 --> 03:22.941
-THAT'S WHERE WE COME IN.

03:24.421 --> 03:25.857
-CAPTAIN, EVEN IF WE LOVE IT,

03:25.988 --> 03:27.729
I MEAN, WE CAN'T AFFORD
A PIECE OF EQUIPMENT

03:27.859 --> 03:29.252
LIKE THIS ON OUR CURRENT BUDGET.

03:29.383 --> 03:31.254
-OH, WE JUST HAVE TO
CUT BACK IN OTHER AREAS.

03:31.385 --> 03:32.560
-[LAUGHING] YEAH, RIGHT.

03:32.690 --> 03:34.083
WE'RE CUT TO THE BONE AS IT IS.

03:34.214 --> 03:36.346
-WHY DON'T WE JUST FIND
OUT IF WE WANT IT FIRST?

03:36.868 --> 03:38.305
THEN WE'LL WORRY ABOUT
HOW TO PAY FOR IT.

03:39.436 --> 03:42.091
SO I'VE INVITED THE
MANUFACTURER'S REP,

03:42.222 --> 03:43.701
A FORMER LIFEGUARD WHO TRAINS

03:43.832 --> 03:45.442
RESCUE PERSONNEL
ALL OVER THE WORLD

03:45.573 --> 03:47.575
TO PUT SCAT TO THE TEST.

03:50.404 --> 03:51.535
-WHAT KIND OF TEST?

03:52.144 --> 03:54.799
-A TEST AGAINST THE BEST
BAYWATCH HAS TO OFFER.

03:58.412 --> 04:00.588
-[AUDIENCE APPLAUDING]

04:00.718 --> 04:01.589
-THANK YOU, THANK YOU,

04:01.719 --> 04:02.503
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

04:02.633 --> 04:03.591
THANK YOU.

04:04.722 --> 04:06.855
THERE YOU ARE, YOU SLY FOX!

04:06.985 --> 04:09.727
YOU BETTER GET YOURSELF
UP HERE RIGHT NOW.
COME ON!

04:09.858 --> 04:11.729
-LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
LET'S GET HIM UP, COME ON!

04:23.045 --> 04:24.307
-WHAT'S THAT FOR?

04:25.003 --> 04:26.178
-WELL I WAS
STANDING OVER THERE,

04:26.309 --> 04:28.529
AND I NOTICED THAT
YOU WERE CRYING.

04:29.181 --> 04:30.531
-IT FEELS WONDERFUL TO CRY.

04:31.183 --> 04:32.402
ESPECIALLY TO GREAT BLUES.

04:33.882 --> 04:34.752
-AH, YEAH.

04:38.060 --> 04:39.061
IT'S HOT IN HERE, HUH?

04:40.758 --> 04:41.890
-I HADN'T NOTICED.

04:42.630 --> 04:45.415
-WELL, IT'S BECAUSE UH, HEAT
RISES AND I'M STANDING AND,

04:45.546 --> 04:47.765
AND YOU KNOW, YOU'RE
SITTING DOWN AND UM...

04:51.813 --> 04:52.640
YOU MIND?

04:52.770 --> 04:53.728
-IF YOU LIKE.

04:55.904 --> 04:57.558
-HI.

04:58.123 --> 05:00.038
MY NAME IS MITCH.
-BUT YOU HAVE TO KNOW I'M
ONLY HERE FOR THE MUSIC.

05:00.735 --> 05:01.910
I MEAN,
YOU'RE AN ATTRACTIVE GUY,

05:02.040 --> 05:03.651
AND I'M SURE YOU'RE
VERY NICE, BUT,

05:04.347 --> 05:05.740
I'M NEITHER IN THE MOOD

05:05.870 --> 05:07.698
NOR THE MARKET FOR A
LIAISON OF ANY KIND.

05:07.829 --> 05:09.744
-WELL, YOU NEVER
KNOW, I MEAN,

05:09.874 --> 05:11.746
THE WAY MY FRIEND
SINGS THE BLUES,

05:11.876 --> 05:14.357
IT COULD BE A MOOD
ALTERING EXPERIENCE.
[CHUCKLING]

05:14.488 --> 05:15.750
-LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

05:15.880 --> 05:18.492
WE ARE IN FOR A
SPECIAL TREAT TONIGHT.

05:18.622 --> 05:21.364
A MAN WITH MUSIC IN HIS SOUL

05:21.495 --> 05:24.541
WHO'S GONNA TRY AND SET
IT FREE IN PUBLIC TONIGHT

05:24.672 --> 05:25.803
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

05:25.934 --> 05:28.066
A REALLY GOOD FRIEND OF MINE

05:28.197 --> 05:32.201
AND A COURAGEOUS HUMAN
BEING, MR. GARNER ELLERBEE.

05:32.332 --> 05:33.594
COME ON, LET'S
GIVE IT UP FOR HIM.

05:33.724 --> 05:35.683
-IS IT REALLY HIS
FIRST TIME ON STAGE?

05:35.813 --> 05:37.772
-YEAH, YEAH, I MEAN
HE'S GOING THROUGH

05:37.902 --> 05:39.513
A MID-LIFE CRISIS, YOU KNOW?

05:39.643 --> 05:41.558
TRYING THINGS HE'S
NEVER TRIED BEFORE.

05:42.167 --> 05:44.256
-NO ONE SHOULD WAIT
FOR A CRISIS TO DO THAT.

06:00.621 --> 06:01.491
[STAMMERING]

06:05.408 --> 06:06.757
[STAMMERING]

06:17.507 --> 06:20.205
-WELL, STRIKES THAT ONE
OFF THE LIST.

06:21.293 --> 06:23.034
-THAT WAS A CRUEL THING TO SAY.

06:23.165 --> 06:24.427
-NO, IT WAS A JOKE.

06:26.951 --> 06:28.083
NO

06:45.840 --> 06:46.710
-BEAUTIFUL, ISN'T IT?

06:48.016 --> 06:49.713
THE WAY IT CHANGES CONSTANTLY.

06:50.714 --> 06:52.368
I COULD LOOK AT
THE OCEAN ALL DAY.

06:53.761 --> 06:54.588
-YEP.

06:56.851 --> 06:58.809
-MITCH TOLD ME
ABOUT LAST NIGHT.

06:58.940 --> 06:59.897
I'M SORRY.

07:01.769 --> 07:03.335
-I WASN'T SCARED UP THERE,

07:03.466 --> 07:04.859
WASN'T NERVOUS IN THE LEAST.
MY THROAT JUST CLOSED OFF.

07:06.774 --> 07:08.210
JUST LIKE THE FLOW OF MY LIFE.

07:09.211 --> 07:10.865
-YOU PUT TOO MUCH
PRESSURE ON YOURSELF.

07:11.474 --> 07:12.693
THAT'S WHY YOUR THROAT CLOSED.

07:13.824 --> 07:15.173
-YOU HAVE DREAMS,

07:15.304 --> 07:17.088
YOU SET GOALS FOR
YOURSELF AND THEN YOU...

07:18.263 --> 07:19.787
WATCH 'EM FALL BY THE WAYSIDE.

07:21.136 --> 07:22.877
-YOU SOUND LIKE MATT
TALKING ABOUT VOLLEYBALL,

07:24.313 --> 07:26.054
AND HE'S NOT HAVING
A MID-LIFE CRISIS.

07:26.968 --> 07:28.491
HE'S HAVING AN
EARLY LIFE CRISIS.

07:29.144 --> 07:30.711
MY GRANDMOTHER'S HAVING
A LATE-LIFE CRISIS

07:30.841 --> 07:32.800
BECAUSE SHE WANTS TO
SWIM THE ENGLISH CHANNEL.

07:34.715 --> 07:37.195
NOBODY'S LIFE FLOW
EVER GETS CLOSED OFF,

07:38.370 --> 07:40.372
UNLESS THEY STOP TRYING
TO LIVE THEIR DREAMS.

07:43.201 --> 07:44.725
WHAT DO YOU WANNA DO
THAT YOU'RE NOT DOING?

07:47.336 --> 07:49.730
-THE LIST IS TOO
LONG, C.J., TOO LONG.

07:52.472 --> 07:54.648
-WE'RE GONNA PUT TWO
VICTIMS OUT IN THE WATER,

07:54.778 --> 07:57.215
YOU'RE GONNA START FROM THE
TOWER AND USE THE WAVERUNNER.

07:57.346 --> 07:58.739
TRACY'LL USE THE HOVERCRAFT

07:58.869 --> 08:00.871
AND WE'LL SEE WHO
GETS THE BEST RESULTS.

08:01.002 --> 08:02.438
-IT'S NOT A FAIR TEST, CAPTAIN.

08:03.047 --> 08:04.396
I KNOW THESE WATERS.

08:04.527 --> 08:05.876
I KNOW THE WAVES, I
KNOW THE CURRENTS.

08:06.529 --> 08:08.444
-SHAN'T DO YOU A BIT OF GOOD.

08:09.053 --> 08:10.838
I WON'T BE AFFECTED
BY THE CURRENTS.

08:12.927 --> 08:17.845
-OH, UH, MITCH BUCHANAN,
MEET TRACY DODSWORTH.

08:18.541 --> 08:20.630
-MR. BUCHANAN AND
I HAVE ALREADY MET.

08:25.592 --> 08:26.462
-HI.

08:29.596 --> 08:33.337
SO YOU SEE GARNER AND I, WE'RE
LIKE BEST FRIENDS AND,

08:33.469 --> 08:35.210
WE YOU KNOW, WE KINDA
DO THAT TO EACH OTHER,

08:35.340 --> 08:36.907
YOU KNOW, HIT EACH
OTHER WHEN WE'RE DOWN

08:37.038 --> 08:38.342
AND GET EACH OTHER
BACK UP AND--

08:38.996 --> 08:40.693
-WELL, I'M AFRAID THAT'S
NOT MY SORT OF FRIENDSHIP.

08:40.823 --> 08:43.653
-NO, NO NO, PROBABLY
NOT BUT IT'S-- IT'S--

08:43.784 --> 08:45.133
IT'S OURS, YOU KNOW?

08:46.090 --> 08:48.571
I TELL YOU WHAT, LET'S
JUST START OVER HERE, OKAY?

08:50.051 --> 08:52.401
YOU WIN THE RACE,
I'LL COOK YOU DINNER.

08:53.010 --> 08:55.099
IF I WIN THE RACE,
YOU COOK ME DINNER.

08:56.710 --> 08:57.537
-YOU WON'T WIN.

08:59.321 --> 09:00.409
-I WON'T?

09:01.845 --> 09:02.716
-YOU WON'T.

09:03.455 --> 09:04.456
-DO WE HAVE A BET?

09:08.983 --> 09:10.332
-I DON'T EAT RED MEAT.

09:22.387 --> 09:23.563
-ARE YOU READY OUT THERE?

09:24.259 --> 09:25.129
-MAN ON BOAT: READY.

09:26.000 --> 09:27.088
-OKAY, GOOD.

09:31.962 --> 09:33.007
GOOD, RIGHT THERE.

09:33.616 --> 09:34.661
-WOMAN: HELP!

09:34.791 --> 09:37.054
-MAN: HEY, WE'RE
OUT HERE! HELP!

09:37.185 --> 09:38.273
-WOMAN: PLEASE HELP!

09:38.403 --> 09:39.361
-ARE YOU READY?

09:42.016 --> 09:43.234
ON YOUR MARK!

09:43.757 --> 09:44.584
GET SET!

09:45.193 --> 09:46.237
GO!

09:46.368 --> 09:50.764
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

10:31.369 --> 10:32.893
-HEY HEY!

10:33.023 --> 10:34.329
-HEY, I'M HERE!

10:35.112 --> 10:36.026
-HEY!

10:36.157 --> 10:39.987
-[EXCITING MUSIC]

11:33.214 --> 11:35.085
-COME ON, HERD UP,
STRAIGHT UP, HERE WE GO!

11:35.216 --> 11:36.173
OVER HIM, OVER HIM.

11:40.612 --> 11:42.005
HERE WE GO!

11:46.531 --> 11:47.881
HERE WE GO, HERE WE GO!

11:48.011 --> 11:48.925
STRAIGHT UP, HERE WE GO.

11:49.056 --> 11:50.057
OVER HIM, OVER HIM.

11:50.927 --> 11:52.624
OH COME ON, GEEZ.

11:53.234 --> 11:54.365
-MAN: BLOCK THIS, BLOCK IT!

11:54.496 --> 11:56.063
-[GRUNTING]

11:58.369 --> 11:59.806
-PRACTICE IS OVER, BROYLES.

11:59.936 --> 12:01.329
TIME FOR YOU TO
GET A NEW PARTNER.

12:01.459 --> 12:03.287
-IF IT ISN'T THE
WALKING WOUNDED.

12:04.245 --> 12:06.377
REFLEX IS ALWAYS LAST
TO COME BACK, SINCLAIR.

12:06.508 --> 12:07.683
-COOL IT, ALEX.

12:09.554 --> 12:11.295
HOW'S YOUR KNEE?

12:11.426 --> 12:12.557
-YOU STEP OUTTA THE WAY AND
I'LL KICK HIM OVER THE NET.

12:12.688 --> 12:14.603
-YOU'RE WASTING MY
VALUABLE PRACTICE TIME.

12:15.125 --> 12:17.258
COME ON, KURT, DROP
THIS LOSER, LET'S GO.

12:18.999 --> 12:20.174
-WHAT'S THE DEAL, KURT?

12:20.304 --> 12:21.131
ARE YOU GONNA KEEP
PLAYING WITH HIM

12:21.262 --> 12:22.045
EVEN THOUGH I'M READY?

12:22.742 --> 12:24.134
-WELL WHAT IF YOU'RE NOT?

12:24.265 --> 12:25.135
ALEX AND I HAVE BEEN
PLAYING GREAT TOGETHER,

12:25.266 --> 12:26.223
WE'VE BEEN WINNING.

12:26.354 --> 12:27.659
I DON'T WANNA MAKE A CHANGE NOW.

12:28.704 --> 12:29.792
-YEAH, BUT WE'RE PARTNERS.

12:30.314 --> 12:31.881
-BUT THIS IS MY LIVELIHOOD.

12:32.012 --> 12:33.665
LOOK, PROVE TO ME
THAT YOU'RE BETTER,

12:33.796 --> 12:34.666
AND I'LL DUMP HIM.

12:36.407 --> 12:38.105
OTHERWISE, I'D RATHER WIN.

12:52.684 --> 12:54.774
-NOW MITCH IS VERY
SENSITIVE ABOUT HIS COOKING,

12:54.904 --> 12:56.166
SO YOU HAVE TO COMPLIMENT HIM

12:56.297 --> 12:58.038
OR HE'LL BE DEPRESSED ALL NIGHT.

12:58.168 --> 13:00.562
-WHY ISN'T A MAN LIKE MITCH
INVOLVED IN A RELATIONSHIP?

13:00.692 --> 13:02.433
-WELL, HE IS, KINDA.

13:03.173 --> 13:04.740
WITH HIS EX WIFE GAIL.

13:06.524 --> 13:08.004
THEY ALMOST GOT MARRIED AGAIN,

13:08.135 --> 13:09.658
BUT IT DIDN'T WORK OUT.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.529
SO I THINK HE'S FINALLY
OPEN TO NEW RELATIONSHIPS.

13:12.487 --> 13:14.228
-WELL, I'M NOT.

13:14.358 --> 13:15.533
SO I HOPE HE DOESN'T THINK
BY COOKING ME DINNER TONIGHT,

13:15.664 --> 13:17.057
IT'S GONNA BE THE START OF ONE.

13:17.187 --> 13:18.580
-WHY AREN'T YOU OPEN
TO NEW RELATIONSHIPS?

13:18.710 --> 13:20.451
ARE YOU SEEING SOMEBODY?

13:20.582 --> 13:23.324
-NO, IT'S JUST THAT I, UM-- I'M
ONLY HERE FOR SUCH A SHORT WHILE

13:23.454 --> 13:26.893
AND I DON'T INTEND TO COMPLICATE
MY LIFE BY FALLING IN LOVE.

13:27.023 --> 13:29.199
-WELL YOU CAN'T STOP
YOURSELF FROM FALLING IN LOVE.

13:30.200 --> 13:31.332
AT LEAST I CAN'T.

13:32.246 --> 13:33.203
-I CAN.

13:33.334 --> 13:34.248
-[LAUGHING]

13:39.427 --> 13:43.039
-HOBIE IS SO INTO MUSIC, HE
CAN'T EVEN HEAR HIMSELF THINK.

13:44.171 --> 13:45.389
-I LOVE ALL SORTS OF MUSIC.

13:45.912 --> 13:47.478
I WAS BORN IN THE OUTBACK.

13:47.609 --> 13:49.872
MY MOM SAID THERE WERE ABORIGINE
DRUMS AND FLUTES PLAYING

13:50.003 --> 13:51.134
WHEN I CAME INTO THE WORLD.

13:51.265 --> 13:52.701
-REALLY? WOW.

13:54.137 --> 13:56.226
HOW'D YOU GET INVOLVED IN
THE HOVERCRAFT, ANYWAY?

13:57.010 --> 13:59.969
-I'VE ALWAYS LOVED THE
IDEA OF FLOATING ON AIR.

14:00.491 --> 14:02.754
AND BEING AN INSTRUCTOR
LETS ME TRAVEL THE WORLD.

14:05.366 --> 14:06.933
-IS THAT WHY YOU DON'T
WANNA GET TIED DOWN

14:07.063 --> 14:08.238
INTO A RELATIONSHIP?

14:09.196 --> 14:10.719
-WHO TOLD YOU THAT?

14:10.850 --> 14:13.548
-C.J. SHE WARNED ME NOT TO
SPIN MY WEB AROUND YOU,

14:13.678 --> 14:14.810
THAT YOU'D BE HERE AND GONE.

14:15.506 --> 14:17.378
UM, I DIDN'T USE ANY
SALT, IS THAT OKAY?

14:17.508 --> 14:18.814
-PERFECT!

14:18.945 --> 14:20.947
I LOVE SPIDER WEBS
IN THE MORNING,

14:21.556 --> 14:22.687
THE BEADS OF DEW ON THEM.

14:23.297 --> 14:24.820
THE SUNLIGHT STREAKING THROUGH.

14:25.952 --> 14:27.692
-DO YOU THINK A
SPIDER APPRECIATES

14:27.823 --> 14:29.129
THE BEAUTY OF ITS OWN CREATION?

14:29.912 --> 14:31.348
-OF COURSE IT DOES.

14:31.479 --> 14:34.264
-I DON'T KNOW, I THINK IT'S
ONLY FOR FUNCTION, YOU KNOW?

14:34.395 --> 14:35.526
CATCH FLIES.

14:39.661 --> 14:40.923
-AM I YOUR FLY?

14:42.794 --> 14:44.927
-NO, YOU ARE ANOTHER SPIDER.

14:45.580 --> 14:46.929
-HMM.

14:47.060 --> 14:48.061
HOW ABOUT STEPHANIE?
WAS SHE YOUR FLY?

14:48.757 --> 14:50.237
-WHO TOLD YOU ABOUT STEPHANIE?

14:51.151 --> 14:53.457
-BOTH: C.J.

14:53.588 --> 14:54.806
-I JUST LOVE HER,
I'M GONNA HAVE TO THANK HER
PERSONALLY TOMORROW MORNING.

14:56.330 --> 14:57.897
-YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK
PEOPLE WHO WORK TOGETHER

14:58.027 --> 14:58.985
SHOULD GET INVOLVED.

14:59.115 --> 15:00.682
IT, UM, COMPLICATES EVERYTHING.

15:00.812 --> 15:03.337
-I DON'T KNOW, COMPLICATIONS
ARE THE SPICE OF LIFE.

15:03.467 --> 15:05.730
-AH, SO YOU LIKE
COMPLICATIONS BUT NOT SALT.

15:05.861 --> 15:09.212
-NO, NO, THEY BOTH CAUSE
HIGH BLOOD PRESSURE.

15:09.734 --> 15:12.346
BELIEVE ME, I DON'T
WANT ANY COMPLICATIONS.

15:13.303 --> 15:16.698
AND I DIDN'T INVITE
YOU HERE TO SEDUCE YOU.

15:20.049 --> 15:22.095
ALTHOUGH YOU ARE
VERY ATTRACTIVE.

15:23.835 --> 15:24.793
-SO ARE YOU, SIR.

15:27.491 --> 15:28.884
-I JUST THINK THAT YOU KNOW,

15:29.015 --> 15:32.888
WE SHOULD LEARN TO WORK
TOGETHER AS FRIENDS,

15:33.019 --> 15:35.369
HAVE SOME FUN, SAVE SOME LIVES.

15:35.499 --> 15:37.371
-[LAUGHING] HOPEFULLY
NOT IN THAT ORDER.

15:37.501 --> 15:38.938
-HOPEFULLY NOT IN THAT ORDER.

15:39.068 --> 15:41.157
AH, I HOPE YOU LIKE
SALMON, IT'S MY SPECIALTY.

15:41.288 --> 15:42.289
-I LOVE IT.

15:43.986 --> 15:45.901
BUT DO YOU THINK
MEN AND WOMEN CAN?

15:47.555 --> 15:48.991
-WHAT?

15:49.557 --> 15:52.299
-BE ATTRACTED TO EACH OTHER
AND WORK TOGETHER AS FRIENDS?

15:54.388 --> 15:55.693
--SURE, WHY NOT?

16:08.924 --> 16:10.447
-KURT: COME ON,
ALEX, RIGHT NOW.

16:12.754 --> 16:13.624
[GRUNTING]

16:17.802 --> 16:19.108
-THINK THEY'RE GOOD?

16:19.239 --> 16:20.066
-THEY'RE AWESOME.

16:20.196 --> 16:24.940
-[CHATTERING]

16:26.898 --> 16:28.030
-THEY HAVE THEIR WEAKNESSES.

16:28.161 --> 16:29.205
HOW ABOUT YOU?

16:29.336 --> 16:30.946
ARE YOU ANY GOOD?

16:31.077 --> 16:32.643
-I'M NOT AWESOME, IF
THAT'S WHAT YOU MEAN.

16:33.253 --> 16:34.471
-NOT ACCORDING TO COACH NEIL.

16:35.646 --> 16:36.604
I HAD YOU CHECKED OUT.

16:36.734 --> 16:37.866
SAID YOU WERE A PLAYER.

16:38.388 --> 16:39.999
-YOU CHECKED ME OUT? WHY?

16:40.129 --> 16:41.304
-I NEED A PARTNER.

16:41.435 --> 16:42.566
-IN THE TOURNAMENT?

16:43.741 --> 16:44.612
-NOT EXACTLY.

16:50.009 --> 16:51.401
-HI TRACE!
-HI!

16:51.532 --> 16:52.837
-SO, HOW'D IT GO LAST NIGHT?

16:52.968 --> 16:54.404
-VERY NICELY, THANKS.

16:54.535 --> 16:55.840
-SO YOU AND MITCH GONNA
SEE EACH OTHER AGAIN?

16:55.971 --> 16:57.016
-AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

16:57.146 --> 16:58.104
-REALLY?

16:58.843 --> 16:59.844
-YES, REALLY.

17:01.716 --> 17:03.457
