20:00.503 --> 20:01.069
ALEX LIKES TO HIT
THAT LINE BALL.

20:02.070 --> 20:03.463
THROW ONE HIGH, TAKE IT
OVERHAND, TAKE IT OVERHAND.

20:03.593 --> 20:05.116
TO YOUR LEFT, TO YOUR LEFT,
COME ON NOW,

20:05.247 --> 20:06.944
HERE WE GO, KEEP TIGHT.

20:07.075 --> 20:08.685
GET YOUR ARMS UP THAT WAY.
KEEP WORKIN', KEEP WORKIN' HARD.

20:09.295 --> 20:10.731
THERE YOU GO, KEEP TIGHT,
KEEP TIGHT, KEEP TIGHT,

20:10.861 --> 20:11.819
THERE WE ARE.

20:11.949 --> 20:13.951
ON YOUR TOES, ON YOUR TOES.

20:14.648 --> 20:15.736
GET THOSE HANDS OUT
IN FRONT OF YOU.

20:18.304 --> 20:20.044
ALL RIGHT, LET ME SHOW
YOU THE BLOCKING SIGNALS.

20:20.175 --> 20:21.568
IF I GIVE YOU ONE,
I'M BLOCKING LINE.

20:21.698 --> 20:23.047
TWO, I'M TAKING ANGLE,

20:23.178 --> 20:24.745
AND FIST, I'M TAKING
THE BALL, ALL RIGHT?

20:24.875 --> 20:25.833
-ALL RIGHT, TIM.

20:25.963 --> 20:26.964
SHOULD I ADJUST MY SERVE?

20:27.095 --> 20:28.314
-LET ME SEE ONE FIRST.

20:36.147 --> 20:37.366
-HOW'S THAT?

20:37.497 --> 20:39.542
-OH THAT'S PERFECT,
DON'T CHANGE A THING.

20:42.632 --> 20:43.851
-C.J.!

20:45.722 --> 20:47.594
THIS IS AMAZING, I'M
LEARNING SO MUCH FROM TIM.

20:47.724 --> 20:48.508
-THAT'S GREAT.

20:48.638 --> 20:49.726
-WATCH!
-MATT!

20:50.901 --> 20:52.076
WILL YOU DO SOMETHING FOR ME?

20:52.686 --> 20:54.122
-SURE, WHAT?

20:54.253 --> 20:55.602
-WILL YOU WEAR THIS IN
THE TOURNAMENT TOMORROW?

20:56.820 --> 20:59.780
-OH, C.J., I CAN'T WEAR THAT.

20:59.910 --> 21:01.869
-WHY NOT?
EVERYBODY WEARS ENDORSEMENTS
ON THEIR CLOTHING.

21:01.999 --> 21:03.392
-IT'S NOT THE SAME.

21:04.263 --> 21:06.569
-ANNEXO OIL STARTS DRILLING
IN THE BAY TOMORROW, MATT.

21:06.700 --> 21:08.484
WE NEED TO MAKE A STATEMENT.

21:08.615 --> 21:10.617
-CAN'T YOU, LIKE, CARRY THOSE
PROTEST SIGNS OR SOMETHING?

21:10.747 --> 21:12.532
-PEOPLE DON'T PAY
ATTENTION TO THOSE.

21:13.272 --> 21:14.925
BUT THEY'LL PAY
ATTENTION TO THIS.

21:17.885 --> 21:19.103
[SIGHING]
-FINE.

21:20.583 --> 21:21.367
[SIGHING]

21:21.497 --> 21:22.629
TIM!

21:30.027 --> 21:31.942
-I'M WATCHING THE
LITTLE LEAGUE WORLD SERIES

21:32.073 --> 21:33.814
AND UH, THE ANNOUNCERS SAYS, OH,

21:33.944 --> 21:37.426
WHICH BOY WILL REALIZE THE
ULTIMATE DREAM OF HIS YOUTH?

21:37.557 --> 21:39.036
AND TEARS ARE
RUNNING DOWN MY FACE.

21:39.167 --> 21:40.299
I'M WATCHING LITTLE
LEAGUE WORLD SERIES

21:40.429 --> 21:42.257
-AND CRYING, THINKING,
IT WON'T BE ME.

21:43.519 --> 21:45.739
-EVERYBODY GOES THROUGH THAT
AT SOME POINT IN THEIR LIFE,

21:45.869 --> 21:46.653
INCLUDING ME.

21:46.783 --> 21:47.915
-[SCOFFS] INCLUDING YOU.

21:48.785 --> 21:49.960
-YEAH.

21:50.091 --> 21:51.222
-WHEN?

21:51.353 --> 21:52.354
YOU'RE NOT ONLY
LIVING YOUR DREAM,

21:52.485 --> 21:53.442
YOU'RE LIVING EVERY MAN'S DREAM.

21:53.573 --> 21:55.357
-WHEN I GO UPSTAIRS TONIGHT

21:55.488 --> 21:56.619
AND GO TO BED ALONE,

21:57.577 --> 22:00.449
CAREER IS NOT THE ONLY THING
THAT CAUSES MID-LIFE CRISIS.

22:00.580 --> 22:02.146
-YOU ARE TELLING ME?

22:03.147 --> 22:04.279
-YEAH, YEAH, ME TOO.

22:05.019 --> 22:06.890
YOURS IS ABOUT CAREER,
MINE'S ABOUT RELATIONSHIPS.

22:07.021 --> 22:08.501
-SHOOT, MINE'S ABOUT THAT, TOO.

22:08.631 --> 22:10.285
-YEAH, WELL I
WANTED ONE SO BADLY,

22:10.416 --> 22:12.156
I ALMOST MARRIED MY EX WIFE.

22:12.287 --> 22:15.072
-YOU DID, DIDN'T
YOU? [LAUGHING]

22:15.203 --> 22:16.291
I'M NOT GOING THAT FAR.

22:16.987 --> 22:17.858
-CHECK.

22:19.120 --> 22:20.730
YOU KNOW, GARNER,

22:20.861 --> 22:24.038
I FIND MYSELF ANALYZING
EVERY WOMAN I'M ATTRACTED TO.

22:24.734 --> 22:26.475
WONDERING, IS SHE THE ONE?

22:27.084 --> 22:28.738
CAN I SPEND THE REST
OF MY LIFE WITH HER?

22:29.260 --> 22:30.784
-AH, YOU CAN'T RUSH
INTO IT LIKE THAT, PARTNER.

22:30.914 --> 22:31.915
-I KNOW.

22:33.352 --> 22:34.570
HAPPENED AGAIN LAST NIGHT.

22:35.658 --> 22:36.485
-WITH TRACY?

22:36.616 --> 22:37.486
-YEAH.

22:38.269 --> 22:40.315
THE SCARY THING IS,
THE ANSWER'S YES.

22:43.710 --> 22:45.015
WHAT PERFECT TIMING, HUH?

22:45.146 --> 22:46.539
SHE'S ONLY IN TOWN
FOR A LITTLE WHILE

22:46.669 --> 22:47.888
AND DOESN'T WANT TO GET
INVOLVED WITH ANYONE.

22:48.976 --> 22:50.325
-WELL, IF I CAN GET
UP ON STAGE AND SING,

22:50.456 --> 22:51.674
YOU CAN GO FOR
THIS RELATIONSHIP.

22:51.805 --> 22:54.198
-NO, YOU WERE ON
STAGE GASPING FOR AIR.

22:54.329 --> 22:56.418
-YEAH, BUT I WENT FOR IT.

22:56.549 --> 22:57.854
-AND YOU PANICKED.
-UH-HUH, YOU WATCH, IT'LL
BE DIFFERENT NEXT TIME.

22:57.985 --> 22:59.290
-YEAH, WELL NEXT
TIME, GIVE ME ADVICE.

23:00.117 --> 23:01.467
-YOU ARE SO STUBBORN.

23:04.426 --> 23:05.601
-CHECKMATE.

23:08.561 --> 23:10.214
[LAUGHING]

23:21.661 --> 23:23.271
[GRUNTING]

23:26.796 --> 23:27.580
THANKS!

23:27.710 --> 23:29.059
[LAUGHING]

23:29.190 --> 23:30.452
-IT'S HARD WORK KEEPING
THE BODY IN SHAPE.

23:32.193 --> 23:33.063
-JOIN ME?

23:33.847 --> 23:34.891
-I CAN'T.

23:35.022 --> 23:36.284
-OH, WHY NOT?

23:37.894 --> 23:38.895
-I'M LEAVING.

23:39.635 --> 23:40.723
-WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

23:48.122 --> 23:49.776
LEAVING, LEAVING?

23:50.472 --> 23:51.995
-I JUST STOPPED
IN TO SAY GOODBYE.

23:53.127 --> 23:54.215
-WHY?

23:54.694 --> 23:56.347
-UNFORTUNATELY, YOU'RE
IN TOO GOOD A SHAPE.

23:56.478 --> 23:57.653
I WOULD'VE BEATEN ANYONE ELSE

23:57.784 --> 23:59.481
BY A MUCH WIDER MARGIN.

24:00.613 --> 24:01.396
-SO?

24:01.527 --> 24:03.267
-SO CAPTAIN RUSSELL INFORMED ME

24:03.398 --> 24:05.095
THAT SINCE OUR
RACE WAS SO CLOSE,

24:05.226 --> 24:08.142
THERE WAS NO COMPELLING
REASON TO JUSTIFY

24:08.272 --> 24:09.883
THE EXPENDITURE ON A HOVERCRAFT.

24:10.492 --> 24:11.624
-NO.

24:11.754 --> 24:13.539
THERE ARE MANY
COMPELLING REASONS.

24:13.669 --> 24:14.844
I'M GONNA GO TALK TO HIM.

24:15.758 --> 24:17.456
-I THINK HE'S PRETTY
MUCH MADE UP HIS MIND.

24:17.586 --> 24:19.893
-DON'T GO ANYWHERE.

24:20.546 --> 24:21.503
-MITCH...

24:23.679 --> 24:24.898
MAYBE IT'S FOR THE BEST.

24:26.029 --> 24:27.683
SOME THINGS JUST
AREN'T MEANT TO BE.

24:27.814 --> 24:29.076
-SOME THINGS ARE.

24:34.211 --> 24:35.474
NO REASON, HE SAID,

24:35.604 --> 24:37.084
NO COMPELLING REASON AT ALL.

24:37.214 --> 24:38.738
HE SAID IT'S YOUR FAULT.

24:38.868 --> 24:40.348
-DID YOU TELL HIM HOW
YOU FELT ABOUT TRACY?

24:40.479 --> 24:42.045
-YEAH.

24:42.176 --> 24:43.569
I DON'T THINK IT WOULD
MAKE A DIFFERENCE, THOUGH.

24:44.700 --> 24:46.485
MAYBE SOME THINGS ARE
JUST MEANT TO BE, HUH?

24:46.615 --> 24:48.095
-YEAH, YOU CAN SAY THAT AGAIN.

24:48.225 --> 24:50.532
HOW DO I STAND A CHANCE
OF WINNING WEARING THIS?

24:50.663 --> 24:52.229
-[LAUGHING]

24:52.360 --> 24:53.709
-WELL LOOK, LOOK, DON'T,
DON'T LET THAT DISTRACT YOU.

24:53.840 --> 24:55.319
YOU JUST CONCENTRATE
ON THE TASK AT HAND,

24:55.450 --> 24:56.625
AND UH, LET YOUR
TALENT COM FORTH.

24:56.756 --> 24:58.758
-LOOK WHO'S TALKING.

24:58.888 --> 25:01.021
-ALL RIGHT, THAT'S OKAY,
YOU BE AT ST. MARK'S
CLUB TOMORROW NIGHT.

25:01.151 --> 25:03.589
I'LL SHOW YOU THAT SOME
THINGS ARE MEANT TO BE
IF YOU JUST DON'T GIVE UP.

25:04.328 --> 25:05.852
-I DON'T BELIEVE
WHAT I JUST HEARD.

25:05.982 --> 25:06.853
-WHAT?

25:06.983 --> 25:08.245
-TELL ME YOU'RE NOT GONNA

25:08.376 --> 25:09.464
ESCORT THAT OIL
COMPANY DIVE TEAM

25:09.595 --> 25:10.987
TO THE DRILL SITE THIS MORNING.

25:11.118 --> 25:14.164
-C.J., THEIR PERMIT
REQUIRES A LIFEGUARD.

25:14.295 --> 25:16.253
-THEIR PERMIT
SHOULD BE REVOKED.

25:16.384 --> 25:18.168
-I AGREE, BUT UNTIL IT IS,

25:18.299 --> 25:20.519
THEIR SAFETY IS
OUR RESPONSIBILITY.

25:21.171 --> 25:22.042
-FINE.

25:22.738 --> 25:23.565
WEAR IT.

25:26.786 --> 25:27.656
-[SIGHING]

